<br>
there are a few undeniable aspects of your wizzyness in fast fights:<br>
<br>
raw damage rate- higher is... better. the faster you can cast, the faster you can do dmg. limited by aggro? it's extra time to deal with your aggro limit.<br>
<br>
spell aggro- some spells have a better dmg:aggro ratios. I &lt;3 my rain spells when applicable as they produce very little aggro for the dmg done. my current figure is 41%, if you can bring forward your tests... please do so!<br>
<br>
resists- this is a killer! a high resisting mob lowers damage, gives aggro: everything bad. my resist rate is at 2.4% for single target DD's from parses for past 2 weeks, on raid, so at least im doing well to balance against resists(rains 23.8%, arly - used less - 21.4%). Debuffs can help, too. Since draughts, I think, do not have an innate aggro-spoofer-thing(like iceflame or how Rains work), I would prefer to use them in the cases where their resist check is important. That's is a lot of cases. Resists can also debuffed. Will it help the fight? Think about it... if it will not detract from the other components of the raid, debuffing with HOS TCOI E'CiBreath which may not be used, will surely improve the dps. <br>
<br>
The Strike of Solusek style of spells hits hard and fast. it leaves more deaggro space, but can be resisted more, produces standard aggro, and does not crit for 7k! I still find much use for the spell for clearing things. When I was doing cod ring a good long while ago, I used SOS quite well in there with pally tanked trash. with the limited dps, I think it helped. <br>
<br>
note - for every situation, I think all of our spells can find their own ideal use unless made obsolete by an upgrade. even draught of thunder has its uses, though id like the stun component removed anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mythal>Mythal</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 4:04:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25467.topic&index=49>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mythal.com/images/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Strike of Solusek</span><hr size=1> Why would you have to do 2 Concussions in between SoS's?<br>
